==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tour
<hw>Tour</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>tour</ets>. See
<er>Turn</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A going round; a
circuit; hence, a journey in a circuit; a prolonged circuitous journey;
a comprehensive excursion; <as>as, the <ex>tour</ex> of Europe; the
<ex>tour</ex> of France or England</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The bird of Jove stooped from his airy <qex>tour</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A turn; a revolution; <as>as, the <ex>tours</ex> of
the heavenly bodies</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Blackmore.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>anything done successively, or by
regular order; a turn; <as>as, a <ex>tour</ex> of duty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Journey; excursion. See
<er>Journey</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tour</ent>⟦br⟧

